This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with temporal activity detection in videos. The use of deep learning models for this task also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The mention of similarity scores and the use of a similarity-based approach could indicate that it belongs to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The use of few-shot learning techniques suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the mention of benchmarks and evaluation metrics suggests that it could belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
